Manchester United win the Manchester derby, defeating reigning league champions Manchester City by a score of 3–2 in the 2012–13 Premier League. Robin van Persie scores a last-minute goal and Rio Ferdinand is injured after being hit by a coin. (ESPN) (Premier League) (BBC)In the UEFA Group I, Spain, the defending World Cup champions, defeats France 1–0, with a Pedro's winning goal at the Stade de France. (BBC) (FIFA)In road bicycle racing, Gerald Ciolek of Germany wins 2013 Milan – San Remo single-day cycling race, the fourth stage of the 2013 UCI World Tour season. (BBC)